TI  - Licensing strategies and blockchain adoption decisions in remanufacturing supply chains considering consumer search behavior
AU  - Liu, Bin
AU  - Huang, Zhen
AU  - Li, Juan
AU  - Yun, Qiaoyun
T2  - COMPUTERS & INDUSTRIAL ENGINEERING
AB  - Environmental friendliness and economic benefits drive the swift development of the remanufacturing industry, where manufacturers generally delegate remanufacturing to third-party remanufacturers through technology license, the fixed or privileged licensing contract. Nevertheless, the lack of transparency in restoring process of remanufactured products trigger consumer search behavior for information, affecting remanufacturer's pricing decision. Blockchain technology enhances the traceability and validity of remanufacturing process, thereby boosting consumer purchase intention. This paper investigates the interplay between licensing strategy and blockchain adoption in a competitive remanufacturing supply chain consisting of a manufacturer and a remanufacturer by considering consumer search behavior. Four game-theoretic models are developed regarding whether to introduce the blockchain and which licensing modes selected. Results show that the unit production cost and fixed licensing fees jointly influence the optimal licensing strategy. As for the remanufacturer, blockchain adoption is generally beneficial under both licensing contracts when the unit production cost and the fixed licensing fee are moderate. Additionally, when consumer search effort is high, the considerable production cost and fixed licensing fee make the adoption of blockchain favorable only under the privileged licensing mode. Lastly, the impact of blockchain on consumer surplus is contingent on the consumer search cost coefficient, which increases consumer surplus only within a specific range. This paper enriches research on the interaction between blockchain introduction and licensing strategy by considering consumer search behavior, offering managerial insights to enhance supply chain transparency, efficiency, and sustainable industrial development.
